Daly_City.The Red Victorian:
The Red Victorian is a historic hotel located in San Francisco's Haight-Ashbury district, two blocks from Golden Gate Park and well served by public transit.
The Red Victorian is a Bed and Breakfast/community space constructed in 1904 in San Francisco's Haight Ashbury District. The building has seen many names and eras - it was originally named the Jefferson Hotel, which is rumored to have been a brothel.
